27/06/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha said Monday (26 June) that the government is considering a series of measures aimed at strengthening the fight against trafficking in humans and drugs. Speaking at a meeting of the state anti-trafficking committee, Berisha said poverty and corruption in state administration were to blame for what he described as a source of "shame" to national dignity. Voicing dissatisfaction with ongoing efforts to combat trafficking, he called for a policy of zero tolerance. (Albanian News, Dan - 27/06/06)
